    "body" : "There is 1) creating a custom exception type/class (as shown so many times) and 2) raising the exception. To raise an exception, simply pass the appropriate instance to <code>throw</code>, normally: <code>throw new MyFormatExpcetion(&quot;spaces are not allowed&quot;);</code> -- you could even use the <i>standard</i> <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/ParseException.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">ParseException</a>, without &quot;creating&quot; a custom exception type."
