    "answer_id" : 8423750,
    "question_id" : 8423700,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Great answers about creating custom exception classes. If you intend to reuse the exception in question then I would follow their answers/advice. However, If you only need a quick exception thrown with a message then you can use the base exception class on the spot</p>\n\n<pre><code>String word=reader.readLine();\n\nif(word.contains(\" \"))\n  /*create custom exeception*/\n  throw new Exception(\"My one time exception with some message!\");\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
