    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As a careful programmer will often throw an exception for a special occurrence, it worth mentioning some general purpose exceptions like <code>IllegalArgumentException</code> and <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/index.html?java/lang/IllegalStateException.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>IllegalStateException</code></a> and <code>UnsupportedOperationException</code>. <code>IllegalArgumentException</code> is my favorite:</p>\n\n<pre><code>throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Word contains blank: \" + word);\n</code></pre>\n"
